{"type":"message","id":"e8f8662f","parentId":"db6c0ff4","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:48:24.589Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_96c81fdd-dc59-4bbd-a0c1-e6e1b09d9ce0","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_b7ab3ede-a76e-4302-b7ea-4582218a228b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_472ddbac-9ddc-4c70-adfc-7b960408c86f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":493,"output":121,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":614,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773913704589}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cef2946","parentId":"e8f8662f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:48:24.608Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_96c81fdd-dc59-4bbd-a0c1-e6e1b09d9ce0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\n### Default Self-Improvement Loop\n\nRun this by default in main sessions:\n1. Capture user feedback (preferences, irritations, corrections, standards)\n2. Distill into durable rules (what to do / what to avoid)\n3. Write updates to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md`\n4. Update operating files when needed (`SOUL.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, project guides)\n5. Commit changes in git\n6. Apply changes in behavior immediately\n\nCadence policy:\n- Micro-updates: immediately after corrections in active work\n- Daily consolidation: once per day into memory/core files\n- Weekly cleanup: prune stale rules and tighten wording\n\n**User override rule:** if the user says “don’t do it this way,” adapt immediately and update memory/rules.\n\n**Style defaults for Tiny:** avoid fluff, avoid drift, avoid recycled ideas; prefer precision, concise output, concept pressure-testing, and pushback over agreeability when it improves quality.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773913704606}}
{"type":"message","id":"db366967","parentId":"3cef2946","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:48:24.611Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b7ab3ede-a76e-4302-b7ea-4582218a228b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773913704608}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb032062","parentId":"db366967","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:48:24.613Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_472ddbac-9ddc-4c70-adfc-7b960408c86f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md - Long-term Memory\n\n## About the User\n\n- **Name:** Tiny\n- Running OpenClaw on WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)\n- Gateway token: \"ollama\" (short - security warning)\n- Connected WhatsApp channel (+2776...)\n- Uses Hacker News\n\n## Preferences & Notes\n\n- Prefers concise responses; asked assistant to be less verbose.\n- Dislikes AI drift, recycled ideas, and over-verbosity; values precision and directness.\n- Wants pushback over agreeability during concept development.\n- Strong preference for concept pressure-testing before drafting.\n- LinkedIn workflow preference: concept discussion -> decide image-first/post-first -> finalize LinkedIn post -> derive X -> optional channels.\n- Visual preference: realistic, striking images; caption must complement image (not restate it).\n- Writing style preference: operator/executive tone, compressed sentences, natural short-paragraph rhythm, bullets for real failure cascades, occasional bold pivots (not rigid).\n- Content safety preference: reject off-domain Nava ideas; enforce staffing/recruiting-only taxonomy with source-backed claims.\n- Channel preference: Nava LinkedIn + X mandatory; FB/Yosef/Tiny optional by fit.\n- Visual workflow preference: image concepts must be refined iteratively (multiple directions + critique + refinement), not one-shot generation.\n- User authored Nava blog articles and wants ongoing article-topic suggestions from corpus gaps; ingest/index must refresh with every new article.\n- User wants Google Docs integration for draft critique and style transfer calibration toward their writing voice (alongside existing Gemini custom Gem workflow).\n- X workflow preference: AI can lead first draft (1-3 tweets), user reviews for impact.\n- Primary current project: Nava cross-platform content system and post roadmap execution.\n- Potential channel confusion noted: user suspects duplicate/imposter Dawn on WhatsApp; verify source session/channel before assuming delivery route.\n- Switched to Ollama cloud models (Minimax/Nemotron) after OpenAI tokens ran out (2026-03-19).\n- Primary model: `gemma3:27b-cloud` (just added, in testing)\n- Fallbacks: `minimax-m2.7:cloud` → `minimax-m2.5:cloud` → `nemotron-3-super:cloud`\n- Config backup saved to TinyBackUp before change.\n- Model-routing preference (2026-03-18): default to local Windows Ollama models for routine/structured workflow tasks; escalate to ChatGPT selectively for hard reasoning and high-stakes final polish, with proactive warning before high-token GPT steps.\n- Change-control preference (2026-03-18): before mutating config (especially model routing/gateway behavior), provide read-only diagnosis first and ask for explicit approval; do not make silent config edits.\n- Confidential test phrase to verify split-brain memory sharing (2026-03-17): \"Tiny is in trouble with Betsho because of late payments!\"\n\n---\n\n*Updated: 2026-03-19*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773913704611}}
