{"type":"message","id":"b133189e","parentId":"61eebac2","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:16:18.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's the thing — `chrome-relay` is a **CDP connection** to your existing Windows Chrome. It doesn't open a new window; it controls the Chrome that's already running on your machine.\n\nSo you'd see it in your normal Windows Chrome, not in a separate window.\n\nAre you running Chrome on Windows right now? If not, open Chrome first, then the relay should connect to it. The CDP port 18792 connects to whatever Chrome instance is running locally with debugging enabled."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.5:cloud","usage":{"input":30769,"output":240,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1773922578726}}
